                <gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="line"/> </ab></div><div n="2" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> <supplied reason="lost">P</supplied>rimia Accepta <lb n="2"/><supplied reason="lost">e</supplied>t <expan><abbr>Privati</abbr><ex>i</ex></expan> Secund<supplied reason="lost">i</supplied><lb break="no" n="3"/>nus et Tertinus <lb n="4"/>et Con<supplied reason="lost">fi</supplied>nis fra<lb break="no" n="5"/>tres ex voto Pri<lb break="no" n="6"/>vati Ter<supplied reason="lost">ti</supplied>ni sup<lb break="no" n="7"/>ra scrip<supplied reason="lost">ti</supplied> <expan><abbr>v</abbr><ex>otum</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex>olverunt</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>l</abbr><ex>ibentes</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>l</abbr><ex>aeti</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>m</abbr><ex>erito</ex></expan>
            </ab></div></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Der Name der Gottheit muss sich auf der corona befunden haben. Auf der linken Nebenseite eine Victoria, auf der rechten Mars dargestellt. Daher vielleicht Weihung an Mars und Victoria, oder Iuppiter Optimus Maximus. (B): CIL 13, 07505; Haug; Brambach; Boppert: kleinere Leseabweichungen.</p>
            </div>
